<!-- guidance: What satisfies it: URL + username + password for the review
org, supplied through the submission channel — NEVER committed to the repo or
pasted into this document. The evidence cell here says "supplied separately"
plus where the runbook lives. What reviewers look for: credentials that log in
cleanly on first try, with MFA disabled for the review accounts (baseline:
testenv-mfa-disabled-for-reviewers) — an MFA prompt makes the org un-testable
and bounces the whole submission (baseline: fail-untestable-environment).
Common mistakes: rotating the password between filling this row and
submitting; org-wide MFA enforcement applying to the review users. Validate
the login the day of submission. Owner-run; see
/sf-security-review-toolkit:prepare-test-environment. -->

