## Row 10 — Third-party credentials + two test users
<!-- baseline: artifact-third-party-creds-two-test-users, mcp-per-user-authz-mechanics -->

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| **Status** | {{ROW10_STATUS}} |
| **Evidence / pointer** | {{ROW10_EVIDENCE}} |
| **Owner** | {{ROW10_OWNER}} |
| **What we provide** | {{ROW10_RESPONSE}} |

<!-- guidance: What satisfies it: credentials for any third-party
resource server the solution integrates with, PLUS two test users with
DIFFERENT permission levels and a documented expected-results matrix: the same
tool call under each user must return only that user's authorized data. The
credentials are supplied separately (Row 1 rule); what this row documents is
WHAT the two users demonstrate — which tool calls, which expected
differences, and where the automated authorization-boundary proof lives
(test file or script path). Fully settled (baseline:
mcp-per-user-authz-mechanics, verified — settled negatively): per-user auth
is not supported by the Agentforce MCP client and NO end-user identity is
forwarded to the server at tool-call time, so write the expected-results
matrix in honest terms — through Agentforce the two users demonstrate
Salesforce-side gating (permission sets / agent + tool access per user) on
top of the partner's TENANT-level scoping; per-user data scoping is proven
at the partner's own API layer. Never promise per-end-user enforcement at
the MCP layer. -->

